<TITLE> 21 killed in road accidents over 36 hours </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 27 (bdnews24.com)At least 21 people were killed and scores more injured in road accidents on crowded highways across the country in the 36 hours up to midday on Eid. Hundreds of thousands scrambled to get out of the capital ahead of Eid-ul-Azha on Saturday, battling through dense holiday traffic to reach home districts in time to celebrate with family. A rush of commuters clogged the nation's highways, ferries were full to bursting and trains crammed full. Anwar Kamal, a superintendent of highway police, told bdnews24.com the number of vehicles rose five to six fold on major roads countrywide on Friday, with most forms of transport carrying passengers far above capacity. The crowded highways and overloaded vehicles led to tragedies that marred the holiday for many families. In Hobiganj, three people were killed and 25 injured as a bus and a truck collided head-on along the Dhaka-Sylhet highway on Saturday, police said. Shayestaganj Highway Police chief Ali Farid said the Dhaka-bound bus collided with the truck at Bahubal in Habiganj at midday. The injured were admitted to Sylhet Osmani Medical College Hospital and Hobiganj General Hospital. In Jamalpur on Friday, three people including a police constable were killed and 40 injured in a bus accident on the Jamalpur-Madarganj highway at around 8pm. Police said the Madarganj-bound local bus fell into a roadside ditch as it lost control near Jotiapara. Eleven among the injured were taken to Madarganj General Hospital and others to different hospitals. In Madaripur, five people were killed and 40 others injured on the Dhaka-Khulna highway at around 11am Friday. The injured were admitted to local hospitals in Faridpur, Bhanga and Shibchar. Shibchar police sub-inspector Sabur Hossain said a Dhaka bound bus collided with a Khulna bound bus killing four passengers on the spot. Another succumbed to injuries in hospital, he said. In Dinajpur, two people were killed after a bus hit their motorcycle on the Dianajpur-Thakurgaon highway at around 6am Friday, police said. A third person, also a passenger on the bike, was admitted to Rangpur Medical College Hospital in a critical condition. In Rajbari, police said five people were killed and 20 others injured in a bus accident on the Doulatdia-Khulna highway near Goaland bus stand. Goaland police sub-inspector Mizanur Rahman said a Jessore bound bus lost control and crashed into a ditch at around 5:30am leaving four passengers dead on the spot. Another died on the way to hospital. Another three people were killed Friday morning in two separate accidents in Tangail, said police. Mirzapur police said a Rangpur bound bus crashed off the Dhaka-Tangail highway leaving two passengers dead and 15 injured, while locals said an unidentified man died after falling from the top of a moving truck in Tangail Sadar Upazila. bdnews2
